    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="230"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d230">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1012a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Ambassador to France</gloss>.</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d230fn1">The same to the Embassies at London and
                        Berlin.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Until there is some material change in the situation, the Department believes the
                    interests both of the lenders and of China would be best served by the several
                    Governments standing firmly by the joint representations made on July 9. But if
                    China finds itself unable to accept the conditions then laid down, it should be
                    left free to make other arrangements to meet its immediate requirements. You may
                    so inform the Government to which you are accredited.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
